                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 819.77/78.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">American Chargé d’Affaires</gloss> to
                        the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Panama</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1911-10-09">
                            <hi rend="italic">October 9, 1911</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>The bill forbidding any loan for constructing the Panamá-David railroad and
                    authorizing use therefor of $6,000,000 now invested in New York, is being rushed
                    through the Assembly. Article 138 of the Constitution is canceled by the
                    bill.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Andrews</hi>.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
